Manage project workspaces: repos, worktrees, and project metadata. Use this to create projects, scan directories for repos, create/remove git worktrees, and check disk usage. When the user mentions working on a specific project or repo, use `list` first to see what's registered, then operate on the right project. When starting a new feature branch, use `create_worktree` to set up a worktree in the project root, then spawn an OpenCode worker in that directory.
